01:33:49,924 --> 01:33:51,653
They're torturing me.

1020
01:33:52,960 --> 01:33:54,052
I see.

1021
01:33:58,599 --> 01:34:01,159
And how'd you like the movie, Truman?

1022
01:34:23,524 --> 01:34:28,359
I frankly don't see what all the fuss is about.

1023
01:35:14,375 --> 01:35:15,307
Hello.

1024
01:35:15,443 --> 01:35:17,638
- Mr. Truman Capote?
- Yeah.

1025
01:35:18,212 --> 01:35:22,012
I have a call from Mr. Perry Smith
in the Kansas Correctional System.

1026
01:35:22,616 --> 01:35:24,516
Will you accept charges?

1027
01:35:25,619 --> 01:35:26,586
Yes.

1028
01:35:26,721 --> 01:35:28,712
Mr. Smith, you're on the line.

1029
01:35:28,856 --> 01:35:29,948
Hello.

1030
01:35:32,126 --> 01:35:33,093
Hello?

1031
01:35:33,227 --> 01:35:34,626
Hello, Perry.

1032
01:35:34,895 --> 01:35:38,558
They let me make a couple of phone calls
before I go down to holding.

1033
01:35:38,699 --> 01:35:41,964
You heard
the Supreme Court rejected the appeal?

1034
01:35:45,573 --> 01:35:47,939
No, I didn't. I hadn't heard that.

1035
01:35:51,612 --> 01:35:52,636
Yeah.

1036
01:35:56,183 --> 01:35:57,411
I'm sorry.

1037
01:36:01,055 --> 01:36:03,683
Yeah. They let me make two phone calls.

1038
01:36:06,393 --> 01:36:09,851
We got a date set for the warehouse,
Dick and me.

1039
01:36:11,398 --> 01:36:14,128
Two weeks and finito.

1040
01:36:15,302 --> 01:36:16,496
April 14.

1041
01:36:20,307 --> 01:36:21,899
Will you visit me?

1042
01:36:23,244 --> 01:36:24,370
Truman?

1043
01:36:52,406 --> 01:36:53,873
It's him again.

1044
01:37:01,048 --> 01:37:04,176
It is utterly inappropriate for me
to talk to him.

1045
01:37:13,761 --> 01:37:14,750
Yes?

1046
01:37:19,500 --> 01:37:22,128
I'm sorry, he won't be able to make it.

1047
01:37:35,082 --> 01:37:37,482
- Hello?
- Mr. Shawn, it's Nelle.

1048
01:37:38,018 --> 01:37:40,179
I just got this telegram. Has he seen it?

1049
01:37:40,855 --> 01:37:42,413
He won't read it.

1050
01:37:42,923 --> 01:37:46,222
- Would you put him on, please?
- Nelle, he won't talk.

1051
01:37:46,660 --> 01:37:50,858
Mr. Shawn, if you have to hold him down
and put the phone on his ear...

1052
01:37:50,998 --> 01:37:52,829
I need to speak to him.

1053
01:37:54,501 --> 01:37:55,729
All right.

1054
01:38:18,025 --> 01:38:19,322
It's Nelle.

1055
01:38:26,533 --> 01:38:27,659
Truman.

1056
01:38:29,703 --> 01:38:33,002
"Miss Nelle Harper Lee and Truman Capote.

1057
01:38:35,009 --> 01:38:38,775
"Sorry that Truman was unable to make it
here to the prison...

1058
01:38:39,246 --> 01:38:41,976
"for a brief word prior to necktie party.

1059
01:38:42,783 --> 01:38:45,547
"Whatever his reason for not showing up...

1060
01:38:46,086 --> 01:38:49,487
"I want him to know
that I cannot condemn him for it.

1061
01:38:52,259 --> 01:38:54,056
"Not much time left...

1062
01:38:55,162 --> 01:38:58,598
"but want you both to know
that I've been sincerely grateful...

1063
01:38:58,732 --> 01:39:02,862
"for your friendship through the years
and everything else.

1064
01:39:04,438 --> 01:39:06,872
"I'm not very good at these things.

1065
01:39:08,008 --> 01:39:11,375
"I have become extremely affectionate
toward you both."

1066
01:39:12,346 --> 01:39:14,780
"But, harness time."

1067
01:39:16,617 --> 01:39:20,018
"Adios, amigos. Your friend, Perry."

1068
01:39:32,599 --> 01:39:35,159
Well, I didn't expect to see you again.

1069
01:39:36,437 --> 01:39:38,371
You can visit for a few minutes.

1070
01:39:43,010 --> 01:39:44,272
- Yeah.
- No.

1071
01:39:50,751 --> 01:39:52,184
Five minutes.

1072
01:39:55,656 --> 01:39:56,953
Well, well.

1073
01:39:59,093 --> 01:40:00,390
He returns.

1074
01:40:01,862 --> 01:40:04,524
I don't know what you must think of me.

1075
01:40:06,333 --> 01:40:09,769
Well, you haven't been foremost
on my mind lately...

1076
01:40:09,903 --> 01:40:11,962
as you can probably imagine.

1077
01:40:15,843 --> 01:40:17,504
You got the letter?

1078
01:40:19,780 --> 01:40:21,077
Yes, I did.

1079
01:40:24,885 --> 01:40:28,616
It's true.
I understand why you didn't want to come.

1080
01:40:30,624 --> 01:40:33,115
I wouldn't be here either if I didn't have to.

1081
01:40:33,260 --> 01:40:34,921
You got that right.

1082
01:40:39,400 --> 01:40:42,267
You know Ricardo donated his eyes
to science?

1083
01:40:43,771 --> 01:40:47,605
Next week, some blind man will be seeing
what Dick used to see.

1084
01:40:48,675 --> 01:40:51,610
Yeah, you could be walking in Denver
or somewhere, Truman...

1085
01:40:51,745 --> 01:40:54,737
and suddenly these eyes
will be staring at you.

1086
01:40:55,449 --> 01:40:57,974
That would be something, wouldn't it?

1087
01:40:58,886 --> 01:41:02,049
It would be. It would be.

1088
01:41:15,969 --> 01:41:17,630
You'll be watching?

1089
01:41:19,239 --> 01:41:21,139
I don't know, I'll be...

1090
01:41:23,510 --> 01:41:24,807
Do you want me to?

1091
01:41:29,950 --> 01:41:31,884
I'd like to have a friend there.

1092
01:41:33,020 --> 01:41:35,352
Okay. Then I will.

1093
01:41:46,266 --> 01:41:47,699
It's all right.

1094
01:42:07,221 --> 01:42:09,155
I did everything I could.

1095
01:42:09,990 --> 01:42:11,014
It's okay.

1096
01:42:21,268 --> 01:42:22,599
I truly did.

1097
01:42:24,538 --> 01:42:25,664
I know.

1098
01:42:34,615 --> 01:42:35,877
It's time.

1099
01:42:46,326 --> 01:42:47,623
Mr. Capote.

1100
01:43:03,810 --> 01:43:04,970
Goodbye.

1101
01:43:05,479 --> 01:43:07,413
You're not rid of us yet.

1102
01:43:08,315 --> 01:43:10,510
- We'll see you in a few minutes.
- I wish I had...

1103
01:43:10,651 --> 01:43:11,948
Mr. Capote.

1104
01:43:12,886 --> 01:43:14,615
- Mr. Capote.
- Goodbye.

1105
01:44:10,244 --> 01:44:11,768
Nice to see you.

1106
01:44:54,921 --> 01:44:56,582
Perry Edward Smith.

1107
01:44:56,923 --> 01:45:00,552
For the crime of murder in the first degree,
by order of the Court of Finney County...

1108
01:45:00,694 --> 01:45:02,719
and the Supreme Court
of the sovereign state of Kansas...

1109
01:45:02,863 --> 01:45:04,558
you are sentenced to hang until you die.

1110
01:45:04,698 --> 01:45:07,531
"I will fear no evil: For thou art with me.

1111
01:45:07,934 --> 01:45:10,164
"Thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me."

1112
01:45:10,304 --> 01:45:12,636
You can say something if you want.

1113
01:45:17,978 --> 01:45:20,173
Is there anybody from the family here?

1114
01:45:21,381 --> 01:45:22,439
No, Perry.

1115
01:45:27,421 --> 01:45:29,082
Well, tell them...

1116
01:45:35,162 --> 01:45:39,394
I can't remember what I was gonna say
for the life of me.

1117
01:45:57,784 --> 01:46:01,049
Our Father who art in heaven,
Hallowed be thy name.

1118
01:46:01,288 --> 01:46:05,418
Thy kingdom come,
Thy will be done on earth, as it is in heaven.

1119
01:46:06,126 --> 01:46:08,492
Give us this day our daily bread.

1120
01:46:08,729 --> 01:46:11,664
And forgive those who trespass against us.

1121
01:46:12,499 --> 01:46:15,957
And lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

1122
01:46:45,632 --> 01:46:47,862
It was a terrible experience...

1123
01:46:51,204 --> 01:46:53,331
and I will never get over it.

1124
01:46:55,609 --> 01:46:58,806
They're dead, Truman. You're alive.

1125
01:47:00,881 --> 01:47:04,408
And there wasn't anything
I could have done to save them.

1126
01:47:07,454 --> 01:47:08,785
Maybe not...

1127
01:47:12,426 --> 01:47:14,894
but, the fact is, you didn't want to.
